 IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
 PROGRAM-ID. PrimeNumber.
 DATA DIVISION.
 WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
 01 NUM PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.
 01 IS-PRIME PIC X VALUE 'Y'.
 01 I PIC 9(4) VALUE 2.
 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
 DISPLAY "Enter a number: ".
 ACCEPT NUM.
 PERFORM CHECK-PRIME
 IF IS-PRIME = 'Y' THEN
 DISPLAY "The number " NUM " is prime."
 ELSE
 DISPLAY "The number " NUM " is not prime."
 END-IF.
 STOP RUN.
 CHECK-PRIME.
 IF NUM < 2 THEN
 MOVE 'N' TO IS-PRIME
 EXIT PERFORM
 END-IF.
 PERFORM VARYING I FROM 2 BY 1 UNTIL I > NUM / 2
 IF NUM MOD I = 0 THEN
 MOVE 'N' TO IS-PRIME
 EXIT PERFORM
 END-IF
 END-PERFORM.
 EXIT.
